<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><dmn:definitions xmlns:dmn="https://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20240513/MODEL/" xmlns="https://kie.apache.org/dmn/_F3140888-6BBB-48D3-9C2C-E3E7C639C855" xmlns:di="http://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20180521/DI/" xmlns:kie="https://kie.org/dmn/extensions/1.0" xmlns:dmndi="https://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20230324/DMNDI/" xmlns:dc="http://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20180521/DC/" xmlns:feel="https://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20240513/FEEL/" id="_976E4592-1808-40DE-8D1C-A5B5ED12AD6E" name="Eligible" expressionLanguage="https://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20240513/FEEL/" typeLanguage="https://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20240513/FEEL/" namespace="https://kie.apache.org/dmn/_F3140888-6BBB-48D3-9C2C-E3E7C639C855"><dmn:description>## Overview
Determines whether a loan applicant is eligible based on their credit score and the ratio of loan amount to annual income.

## Inputs
- CreditScore (number) — applicant's credit score.
- LoanAmount (number) — requested loan amount.
- AnnualIncome (number) — applicant's annual income.

## Do not use when
- AnnualIncome is zero or null (division by zero in LoanAmount / AnnualIncome).
- Inputs are unavailable or unverified.

## Main entry points
- Eligible (boolean) — returns true if the applicant passes all eligibility checks, false otherwise.</dmn:description>
  <dmn:extensionElements/>
  <dmn:decision id="_58B142C5-7B61-43D5-9C87-AE6FB87991AD" name="Eligible"><dmn:description>## What it decides
Whether the loan applicant is eligible (true) or ineligible (false).

## Call when
- CreditScore, LoanAmount, and AnnualIncome are all known and AnnualIncome &gt; 0.

## Do not call when
- AnnualIncome is zero or null (causes division by zero in the input expression LoanAmount / AnnualIncome).
- CreditScore is null.

## Inputs
- CreditScore (number) — minimum threshold is 600.
- LoanAmount / AnnualIncome (number) — computed debt-to-income ratio; must not exceed 10.

## Output
`true` — applicant meets all criteria.
`false` — applicant fails at least one criterion (score &lt; 600 OR ratio &gt; 10).

## Examples
- CreditScore=720, LoanAmount=50000, AnnualIncome=30000 → ratio=1.67 → `true`
- CreditScore=550, LoanAmount=10000, AnnualIncome=50000 → score &lt; 600 → `false`
- CreditScore=700, LoanAmount=600000, AnnualIncome=50000 → ratio=12 &gt; 10 → `false`</dmn:description>
    <dmn:extensionElements/>
    <dmn:variable id="_E7A1D59A-3FC3-4F77-B01B-FAFA8A37996E" name="Eligible" typeRef="boolean"/>
    <dmn:informationRequirement id="_518A00D1-3929-4A0E-B699-782893ECE817">
      <dmn:requiredInput href="#_32BD124A-6BCE-455B-90D6-44357B5412CA"/>
